\par 
\par Close to both parents. Father \lquote extremely fond\rquote  of his children. Children sent to St Paul\rquote s daily rather than to boarding schools.
\par 
\par (p 5 transcript) Of teachers, Eynon Smith was a great influence; taught in a Socratic way, provocative debating. But two years only. Also Walter Oakeshott, High Master, \lquote exciting\rquote  weekly sessions. Otherwise not well taught.
