\i\f40\fs22\insrsid14105049\charrsid13525080 Political Change in Britain }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid14105049\charrsid13525080 (1969) with Donald Stokes, had the \lquote good ideas\rquote 
, but too slow, perfectionist. Book based on sample surveys in five nations. Became an election series, later taken over by Essex, then Manchester, and finally back to Nuffield. The statistical appendices in each volume, becoming 
more sophisticated, done by others. Stokes\rquote  general theme was the inheritance of political attitudes from parents.  DB wanted to be a \lquote contemporary historian\rquote 
. They brought out the election books in three or four months, criticised as \lquote indecent haste\rquote . Pupils wrote essays on other earlier elections.
\par 
