\par Repeats story of 1960 Michigan conference and winning support from Norman Chester for joint project: lea
ding to five national surveys and book with Stokes, 50 people in eight constituencies, questionnaire, coded answers, with some open-ended questions. Stokes his cleverest co-author, \lquote shaped the book (1969, still in print), DB \lquote 
production manager\rquote . Series books taken over by Ivor Crewe at Essex, then Tony Heath back at Nuffield, then Jane Green at Manchester. Still going as British Electoral Study; archived in UK Data Archive. They were \lquote trailblazers\rquote 
, the first national academic survey carried out by commercial opinion pollsters.
\par 
