\par DB described in 1950s as \lquote Britain\rquote s foremost electoral statistician\rquote , but he was \lquote totally unqualified, mathematically\rquote 
.  Can work out percentages but never got to calculus. So by late 1950s overtaken by people who were mathematically competent. But thins that statistics should not take over and exclude personalities, public relations, which are harder to measure.
